    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>JD-core-java <a href=\"https://github.com/nviennot/jd-core-java\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/nviennot/jd-core-java</a> is a thin wrapper of jd-core. the readme file shows how to use it in your project.</p>\n\n<pre><code>/* Returns the source of SomeClass from compiled.jar as a String */\nnew jd.core.Decompiler.decompile(\"compiled.jar\", \"com/namespace/SomeClass.class\");\n\n/*\n * Returns the sources of all the classes in compiled.jar as a Map&lt;String, String&gt;\n * where the key is the class name (full path) and the value is the source\n */\nnew jd.core.Decompiler.decompile(\"compiled.jar\");\n\n/*\n * Returns the number of classes decompiled and saved into out_dir\n */\nnew jd.core.Decompiler.decompileToDir(\"compiled.jar\", \"out_dir\");\n</code></pre>\n"
