    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm using <code>procyon-decompiler-0.5.30.jar</code> from its Bitbucket <a href=\"https://bitbucket.org/mstrobel/procyon/downloads/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">repo</a>.</p>\n\n<p>If you need to decompile one or more jars, please copy them to a folder and then run:</p>\n\n<pre><code>%JAVA_HOME%\\bin\\java -jar c:\\procyon\\procyon-decompiler-0.5.30.jar -o . *.jar\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In the above command I'm specifying the full path to the <code>procyon</code> jar, and the <code>-o .</code> sets the output to the current folder.</p>\n\n<p>Lets say I want to check <code>sentry-logback-1.5.4.jar</code>, after running the above command I will end up in the working folder with the following structure:</p>\n\n<pre><code>sentry-logback-1.5.4.jar\n[io]\n  `-- [sentry]\n          `-- [logback]\n                 `-- SentryAppender.java\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 25223771,
      "reputation" : 511,
      "user_id" : 19059901,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/wzMFz.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Heisenbug",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19059901/heisenbug"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763389638,
    "creation_date" : 1763389638,
    "answer_id" : 79822415,
    "question_id" : 22189897,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Inorder to <code>get source code as string</code> from <code>procyon v0.6.0</code> for further processing or any usecase of yours, heres the code you can use :</p>\n<pre><code>private static String callProcyonDecompiler(String className, List&lt;String&gt; jarsPath) {\n    try (StringWriter writer = new StringWriter()) {\n        DecompilerSettings settings = DecompilerSettings.javaDefaults();\n\n        List&lt;ITypeLoader&gt; loaders = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        for (String jarPath : jarsPath) {\n            loaders.add(new JarTypeLoader(new JarFile(jarPath)));\n        }\n        CompositeTypeLoader composite = new CompositeTypeLoader(loaders.toArray(new ITypeLoader[0]));\n        InputTypeLoader inputWrapper = new InputTypeLoader(composite);\n\n        settings.setTypeLoader(inputWrapper);\n        settings.setIncludeLineNumbersInBytecode(true);\n        settings.setRetainRedundantCasts(false);\n        settings.setShowSyntheticMembers(false);\n        settings.setForceExplicitImports(true);\n\n        PlainTextOutput output = new PlainTextOutput(writer);\n        Decompiler.decompile(className, output, settings);\n\n        return writer.toString();\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n    }\n    return null;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
